{
  "stem": "1765.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We had what you might call garden apartments around a big courtyard, with beautiful flowers, and a large lilac tree in front of my father's study.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And when I was born, my parents planted a little white lilac bush next to this huge, beautiful, purple French lilac.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I never had to worry about having playmates, because they were all next door, and the door after that, and upstairs.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And my grandparents lived across the stairwell.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And it was an enclave.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was a self-contained little paradise.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I went to school, to a Yiddish-speaking folkshul, which means that every subject was conducted in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "My mother graduated from a gymnasium, where all the subjects were also taught in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And it was one of the few-- it was the only gymnasium in that part of the world, or in Poland, where the students who studied every subject in Yiddish could go straight to a state university, without having to go for a two-year program in a Polish-speaking school.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We were just wealthy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I mean, I used to feel guilty about it, because in the folkshul which I attended, the tuition was paid by some of the wealthy children's families.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But most of the students-- many of the students-- my school's name was Sofia Markovna Gurewicz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And many of the students came from sometimes impoverished homes, and sometimes middle class, lower middle class, working people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had a lot of friends who would come to my apartment, and I would have every toy in the world.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was enormous by other standards.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One of my best friends lived with her mother in one room.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I used to think, why do I have so much and they don't?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I don't say that was a good feeling.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
